==Arabic==

===Etymology===
Root: [[شجر]] 

===Noun===
'''شَجَرٌ''' (šajar) ''m (collective)'', '''ٌشَجَرَة''' (šajara) ''f (singulative)'', '''شَجَرْتَيْنِ''' (šajartēn) ''(dual)'', '''شَجَرَاتٌ''' (šajarāt) ''([[plural]])'', '''أشْجَارٌ''' (ašjār) ''(pl.)''

# [[tree]]

===Derived terms===
*شَجَرٌ (šajar) = trees (in general) ''(plural in meaning, but grammatically singular)''
*ٌشَجَرَة (šajara) = a tree
*شَجَرْتَيْنِ (šajartēn) = two trees
*شَجَرَاتٌ (šajarāt) = 3 to 10 trees, some trees, a few trees
*أشْجَارٌ ('ašjār) = (kinds of) trees

